metadata.name: Permutation City #227
metadata.description:
The work is inspired by the novel Permutation City by Greg Egan, the author of the hard science fiction.

It raises the issue of whether we can in principle understand that we exist in reality or in a simulation.

According to the Theory of Dust (which is described in the novel), the universe is simulatable and all other possible universes are equally as real as ours, emerging spontaneously from their own mathematical self-consistency. Human consciousness is Turing-computable, which means that consciousness can be also produced by a computer program.

The Autoverse is an artificial life simulator, a massive complex cellular automaton universe, producing cities and the consciousness of human copies.

Gradually, due to failures and a lack of computing power, the idea of the reliability of such universes is destroyed. 

Spaces crumble, cities become fluid and drain down, turning into dust and digital glitch.

Thanks to Yulikolay for helping with code, using p5.Riso.js library for generating files suitable for risograph printing.
Source images for permutation cities are made with a help of DALL·E mini neural network.

metadata.name: The beauty of imperfection #144
metadata.description:
Drawing shapes repeatedly, spinning and rotating. I use basic shapes like square, rectangle, and triangle to create this art. Regular shapes are perfect but it's a little bit boring, so I make them imperfect, just like "hand drawing". I also tried to make this generative art great for physical print, so that I can hang it on the wall. Here we go.

5 background colors:
Black, White, Blue, Green, and Red

Press “space” to play animation.
Press “s” to save.

Made with p5js.
Created by Costa C. | OneRocket.nft

metadata.name: miniGlyph #176
metadata.description:
In celebration of #tezos4tezos I am releasing this mini version of a more complex work in progress. 

Every 24th mint (ex: 1, 24, 48, 72, etc) will receive a free physical woodcut.
https://alleditions.art/p/miniglyph

This project is designed such that it can export a layered vector SVG that can be used for plotting or cutting out of wood with a laser or paper with a Cricut.

Shift P - Export a PNG
Shift S - Export an SVG
Shift E - explode the layers

metadata.name: Urban skyline #33
metadata.description:
"The ragged skyline of the city resembled the disturbed encephalograph of an unresolved mental crisis." [J.G. Ballard]

The work presents the abstraction of an architectural skyline with a sail structure in the foreground rotating around its vertical axis and a background of skyscrapers. Colors are assigned through a limited number of selected palettes.

metadata.description: A randomly-generated PNG Layered digital-pencil representation of Nature. No Code has been used other than Pure Spider's Fxhash Framework Template. Inspiration from (but no affiliation) with Zancan.

metadata.name: Altered #106
metadata.description:
Adj. Changed in character or composition, typically in a comparatively small but significant way.

Please note that the display is progressive and can take some time to finalize.

Artwork by Patrice Orenes-Lerma - @patxol - 2022
Made with math, love & p5js.
CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

Features include :

- 20 color palettes (10 standard, 10 rare)
- 8 palette progression types
- 3 aspect ratio (Portrait is standard, 1:1 and landscape are rare)
- 8 Alteration types
- 3 Alteration power levels
- 5 types of symmetry
- 3 densities
- Spaced mode and Sharp mode

metadata.name: Perpetual Oscillations  #47
metadata.description:
Planes expand and contract over time in different rhythms. 

Display notes:
The work is intended to be viewed running live in the browser, and there is no set aspect ratio. The viewer is invited to explore the space and choose their viewpoint. 

Controls:
Left-clicking and dragging - rotate around the center 
right-clicking and dragging - pan around the space 
Scrolling - zoom in and out 
Press b - b-side 
Press o - go back to the origin 
Press 1 to 3 - change the pixel density
Adjusting pixel density or changing the screen size will bring you back to the origin. 

License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

Made with p5.js

metadata.name: Harlequins #235
metadata.description:
Harlequins

---

WebGL2, a fast GPU will make it more enjoyable. There's an initial pre-compute phase for the animation and that can pause a slow GPU for a few seconds.

---

Harlequins is an exploration in generating beautiful color and texture out of often-discordant beginnings. Much like our world.

Each Harlequin has random materials, background, and a random number of moons around it. Each frame adds more painted light and turns the initial harsh scene into a dreamlike blending of color, creating smooth matte colors on the central orb.

Harlequins is the result of a few months of generative work and lookdev on top of older long-exposure path tracing shaders. The runner and custom WebGL lib are written in TypeScript, lot of GLSL for the fragment shaders, then the whole thing is compiled, minified, and inlined into the final single self-contained HTML file. 6.4k zipped.


Ilmari Heikkinen 2022. Have fun.

---

Press space to enter the display mode. The display mode generates infinite new variants of your minted scene, displaying each one for a short while. Great for chilling out for a bit.

Press s to take a screenshot.

Double-click to render a new variant.

metadata.name: Colin #84
metadata.description:
Finally, the avatar project you've all been waiting for. Profile pictures that truly reflect our unique personalities. A chance to show how individual we are.

With a wide range of clothes and hairstyles, expressions ranging from 'Existential Dread' to 'Overwhelming Anxiety', and exciting colours from 'Brilliant Beige' to 'Wonderful Wheat', it's time to bring some sparkle to Web3.


*Please note, all Colin's will almost certainly look the same*


Contact @iamnotwal if you'd like to be added to the Beige-List!


(Layered compositions made possible because of @PureSpider's generously shared template.)

metadata.name: CharitableKidzCollective #78
metadata.description:
FYI: This is an *unofficial* CyberKidzClub derivative project made with love & respect for CKC.

This collection is heavily inspired by "The CyberKidz Club," a collection of 6666 kids on Tezos. The CKC community donated 1,3866 XTZ worth of backpacks & school supplies to kids in Rocio, Petrópolis early February.

Shortly after this, Petrópolis experienced a tragic storm that has impacted and will continue to impact communities for some time, as families mourn and infrastructure gets rebuilt.

== This project's sole goal is to raise money for the families & communities affected by the landslide ==

All proceeds from this project's initial sale will go towards helping those affected by the landslide in Petrópolis, Brazil. Secondary sales will be donated as long as they can be kept up with.
